YEAR 2015 RESULTS.

CONSUMER SALES TOTALED $4.4 BILLION, DOWN 2.2 PERCENT IN U.S. DOLLARS. ORGANIC LOCAL-CURRENCY SALES INCREASED 3.4 PERCENT, AND FOREIGN CURRENCY TRANSLATION REDUCED SALES BY 5.6 PERCENT.

ON AN ORGANIC LOCAL-CURRENCY SALES BASIS.

·

